<Author>KMF_8
<Content>GREAT new hotel in Boston I'm a frequent business traveler but was in Boston over Thanksgiving to see family and I didn't want to stay in a big hotel like I would normally do. The Inn was exactly what I was looking for! First, the location is amazing- pretty much in the center of Boston (but on a quiet residential street) within walking distance of the Prudential, Copley, the south end, Boston common, Fanuiel hall- you name it. The building itself is a beautiful old brownstone (you would never know it was a hotel if it weren't for the small sign by the door). Parking at the Pru was about 1.5 blocks away. The european style check-in (no front desk, just a code to punch in at the front door) was incredibly convenient- no waiting in lines in the lobby, no having to deal with hotel staff- we just went straight up to our room. The interior is beautifully decorated- the halls, the rooms, the bathrooms- all of it is done very tastefully and artfully. The bed was very comfortable, the sheets were high thread count, and I appreciated the selection of pillows (I hate when hotels don't provide you with a few options). I loved the large windows overlooking the street (and the fact that I could black them out at night). I stayed in the 1 bedroom suite and it was very spacious and well equipped (bathrobe, flat screen tv- the kitchenette even had champagne glasses). The shower was wonderful. In the morning we went down to the continental breakfast (good coffee selection) where I talked to one of the hotel employees, Mike, who was very friendly and extremely knowledgeable about the city and was able to give me a several suggestions for places to eat and sites to see while I was in town.Overall, I had a great stay- I will definitely be coming back to the Inn on future trips, both personal and business. 
